memberdef.name: THROW
memberdef.initializer: do { \ std::stringstream ss{}; \ ss << __FILE__ << ":" << __LINE__; \ throw TYPENAME{ss.str()}; \ } while (false)

memberdef.name: UNIMPLEMENTED
memberdef.initializer: do { \ std::stringstream ss{}; \ ss << "given class \'" << NAME \ << "\' is valid OpenSCENARIO element, but is not yet implemented"; \ throw ImplementationFault{ss.str()}; \ } while (false)

memberdef.name: THROW_UNSUPPORTED_ERROR
memberdef.initializer: [&](auto && child) { \ std::stringstream ss{}; \ ss << "given class \'" << child.name() << "\' (element of class \'" << PARENT.name() \ << "\') is valid OpenSCENARIO element, but is not supported"; \ throw SyntaxError(ss.str()); \ return unspecified; \ }

memberdef.name: UNSUPPORTED
memberdef.initializer: [&](auto && node) { \ std::stringstream ss{}; \ ss << "given class \'" << node.name() \ << " is valid OpenSCENARIO element, but is not supported"; \ throw SyntaxError(ss.str()); \ return unspecified; \ }
